{"accepted":[{"assertion":"Formal-Conjectures statement: Erdos463.erdos_463 https://google-deepmind.github.io/formal-conjectures/theorem/?name=Erdos463.erdos_463.","id":"vf_de1d312edb733128","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Erdős Problem #463: declared status 'open'. Formalized: yes. Is there a function $f$ with $f(n)\\to \\infty$ as $n\\to \\infty$ such that, for all large $n$, there is a composite number $m$ such that\\[n+f(n)<m<n+p(m)?\\](Here $p(m)$ is the least prime factor of $m$.) Prize: no. Tags: number theory, primes.","id":"vf_ea00108575691bbf","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"}],"accepted_activity":false,"activity":[{"accepted":false,"banked":true,"claim":"Reduced Erdos #463 to a clean self-contained criterion: the answer is YES iff g(n)->infinity, where g(n)=max{m-n : m composite, m-n<p(m)}. Gave an explicit construction (p-rough unique multiple of a p","claimed_status":"verified_computationally","classification":"legacy_attempt","id":"vat_1ea0062351203339","kind":"partial_proof","lifecycle":"banked","location":"current_commit","mathematical_scope":"partial","method_channel":"","method_families":[],"named_obstructions":[],"related_problems":[],"remaining_obligations":[],"source_ref":"frontier.json#vat_1ea0062351203339","trust":"signed"},{"accepted":false,"banked":true,"claim":"Erdos #463: lean/Vela/Erdos463.lean proves the square-root finite-search bound for qualifying offsets, and scripts/erdos463_margin_search.py exactly recomputes g(n)=max{d>0 : n+d is composite and d<minFac(n+d)} for n<=10000000; this is finite-prefix evidence only and leaves g(n)->infinity open.","claimed_status":"verified_computationally","classification":"legacy_attempt","id":"vat_6bc66f5f2f436c5f","kind":"vela.erdos_problem_attempt_record_draft.v1","lifecycle":"banked","location":"current_commit","mathematical_scope":"partial","method_channel":"erdos-problems","method_families":[],"named_obstructions":[],"related_problems":[],"remaining_obligations":["lean